	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Yet another Ford Kuga has burst into flames. This time as a Ford employee was taking a client's vehicle for a test drive in Johannesburg. Watch.WATCH Five people were injured after a after a taxi rolled over on Henley On Klip Drive between Johannesburg and Vereeniging on Thursday. When ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene, several passengers were found scattered around the scene, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said. "Paramedics assessed the [passengers] and found that two had sustained serious injuries while three other patients had sustained minor to moderate injuries," he said. "[They] were treated for their injuries, and the two seriously injured provided with pain-relief medication, before they were transported to Kopanong and Sebokeng provincial [hospitals] for further treatment." Meiring added that local authorities were investigating the accident. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  